<http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl/2/hasPolicy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "ODRL: attaches an ODRL policy to a resource. Range restricted to odrl:Policy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#hasDeployment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has deployment"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#hasOfferPolicy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links an offering to the ODRL offer policy that governs the offered model. Functional: each offering carries exactly one canonical offer policy."@en .
<http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/isPrimaryTopicOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing> .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#contextTask> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The it6:Task the evaluation context is defined over. Functional."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#CrossParticipantProvenanceRecord> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "When a derived artefact is produced by a consumer invoking a provider's model hosted by a third-party operator, a CrossParticipantProvenanceRecord aggregates the relevant activities across the provider, consumer, and operator participant contexts into one bundle for audit."@en .
<http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl/2/assignee> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "ODRL: the party receiving the policy rules."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#authorizedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#authorizesRun> .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#ParticipantRole> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A dataspace-scoped role played by a participant with respect to AI assets (anti-rigid; an agent gains and loses roles over time)."@en .
<http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/isPrimaryTopicOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing> .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#IOContract> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The minimum machine-actionable invocation contract for a deployment: input format, output format, authentication method, and optional input/output schemas."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#GovernanceActor> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "An external compliance body that reads CrossParticipantProvenanceRecord bundles and AuditEvidence records to verify lawful execution holds a GovernanceActor role — for example, a regulator or a conformance-labelling body."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#CrossParticipantProvenanceRecord> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "cross-participant provenance record"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#expiresAt> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Expiry timestamp of the execution authorisation."@en .
<http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Association> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Association"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#GovernanceActor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Role of an agent that audits execution evidence, enforces compliance obligations, and validates governance across the dataspace."@en .
<http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/primaryTopic> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/> .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#integrityHash> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links audit evidence to an spdx:Checksum that bundles the algorithm (spdx:algorithm) and the digest value (spdx:checksumValue). Functional: exactly one canonical checksum per evidence record. A plain-string digest without its algorithm cannot be verified, so a structured spdx:Checksum is required rather than an xsd:string."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#inParticipantContext> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/edc/v0.0.1/ns/ParticipantContext> .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#DerivedArtifact> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "When a consumer invokes a deployed model, the run's output (a prediction dataset, a classification result, a generated artefact) is typed as a DerivedArtifact that points back to the producing run (daimo:derivedFromRun) and to the authorisation under which it was produced (daimo:underAuthorization)."@en .
