<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "DAIMO is an integration profile that connects DCAT-AP, MLDCAT-AP, ODRL, PROV-O, and the Dataspace Protocol (DSP, as operationalised by Eclipse EDC) to support publication, discovery, invocation, execution traceability, and contextualised evaluation of AI model assets exchanged in data spaces. The edc: namespace is used only for EDC-specific extensions (e.g., ParticipantContext) not yet standardised in DSP."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#Evaluator> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Role of an agent that evaluates or compares AI models under a shared evaluation context."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#ExecutionAuthorization> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ODRL agreement (produced by a DSP contract negotiation) that binds at least one odrl:permission to concrete it6:Run invocations it authorises. Specialises odrl:Agreement; MUST carry at least one odrl:permission per the ODRL policy model."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#offeredBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent> .
