<http://data.europa.eu/it6/Run> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MLDCAT-AP: a concrete execution of an algorithm over data, producing outputs and evaluations. Specialises mls:Run."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#SharedEvaluationContext> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#TopLevelKindsDisjointness> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Asserts that the nine top-level DAIMO-native kinds are pairwise disjoint. ParticipantRole subclasses are deliberately excluded so that a single agent may simultaneously hold several roles (e.g., a research group acting as both Evaluator and Model Provider)."@en .
