<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#exposedAs> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a deployment to the DCAT data service(s) that expose it. Non-functional: one deployment may expose multiple endpoints (e.g., a REST service plus a gRPC service, or regional load-balanced endpoints). Each service's I/O contract can differ (see daimo:hasIOContract, also non-functional)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#hasAuditEvidence> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#evidenceOf> .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#ModelProvider> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Role of an agent that publishes AI models as governed offerings in a dataspace catalog."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pionera/daimo#onInfrastructure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a deployment to the MLDCAT-AP computer infrastructure running it. Functional: one deployment runs on one canonical infrastructure instance (redundancy is modelled as multiple deployments)."@en .
